      "cooked": "<p>Thanks David.  Power smoothing make it so the actual power number does not jump around so much and stays more of a 3-second or \u201csmooth\u201d average.  This makes it so you can clearly see you are generally at say 150w vs your 140w target.  Which helps a bit but yes I understand generally what you mean by color now indicating how close you are to being on track.  We could turn this feature on for non-ERG mode.  I like the idea.  Need to just look at TR and have my designer try a few ideas on how it might look.</p>",
